text.section:
A person has notice of a fact if the person:
Knows of it;
Has received a notification of it;
Has reason to know it exists from all of the facts known to the person at the time in question; or
By reason of a filing or recording to the extent provided by and subject to the limitations set forth in KRS 362.1-303(4) or (5), 362.1-704(3), or 362.1-805(3).
